<h1>To Jonathan Boucher</h1>

<div class="docbody">
<div class="opener">
<table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Dear Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Mount Vernon Jan. 2st 1771</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Jacks return has been delayd, as well from a belief that you might not be well settled, or from a desire of gratifying him in his favourite amusement of Hunting, these Hollidays<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0001" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0001-ptr">1</a>He returns now he says, with a determination of applying close to his Studies; and I confide entirely in your promise of making him do so, as time slips of a pace, and other Ideas &amp; pursuits, will soon render it more difficult to keep him confind to them, than at present. In respect to the kinds, &amp; manner of his Studying,
<span class="pb" title="page number in print edition (no page scan available)" id="GEWN-02-08-02-pb-0426">[426]</span>
I leave it wholely to your better judgmenthad he begun, or rather pursued his Study of the Greek Language, I should have thought it no bad acquisition; but whether to acquire this now, he may not forego some more useful branches of learning, is a matter worthy of considerationTo be acquainted with the French Tongue, is become a part of polite Education; and to a Man who has any idea<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0002" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> of mixing in a large Circle, absolutely necessary. Without<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003-ptr">3</a> Arithmetick, the common affairs of<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0004" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0004-ptr">4</a> life are not to be managed with success. The study of Geometry,<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0005" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0005-ptr">5</a> and the Mathematics (with due regard to the branches<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0006" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0006-ptr">6</a> of it) is equally advantageous. The principles<a class="ptr" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0007" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0007-ptr">7</a> of Philosophy, Moral, Natural, &amp;ca I should think a very desirable knowledge for a Gentleman; but as I said before, I leave the whole to your direction; with this earnest request that, in whatever kind of Study you think proper to engage him, he may be kept diligently to it, for he really has no time to loose.</p>
<p>The shortness of the distance between this and your present habitation will, I hope, give us the pleasure of seeing you and Miss Boucher often at Mount Vernon; in this hope Mrs Washington also rests, and with her Compliments and wishes, joind with mine for the return of many happy, &amp; prosperous years to you, I remain with great sincerety Dr Sir Yr Most Obedt Hble Servt</p>
<div class="closer">
<p class="signed">Go: Washington</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Autograph Letter Signed: a letter in the handwriting of, and signed by, the author ]">ALS</abbr> (photocopy), <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 GW originally dated the letter 1st. This letter is badly mutilated. A large portion is missing from the bottom of the letter, and in its place a piece of paper has been inserted which contains in another hand a few words, most of which are too faded to be legible. GWs letter of 2025 Feb. 1771 to Boucher contains a similar repair and insertion. The letter was printed in <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Lippincotts Monthly Magazine</span> (May 1889), 728, with the missing portions in square brackets.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>John Parke Custis arrived with Boucher at Mount Vernon for his holiday on 4 December.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>These words in another hand are legible in the repaired section. The copy of the letter printed in <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Lippincotts Monthly Magazine</span> reads, the prospect. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0289&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0289-sn#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-sn" class="document">source note</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>These words are taken from <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Lippincotts</span>. See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0289&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0289-sn#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-sn" class="document">source note</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0289&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003" class="document">note 3</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0005-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0005">5</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0289&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003" class="document">note 3</a>.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0006-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0006">6</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0289&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003" class="document">note 3</a>. <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Lippincotts</span> has, incorrectly, [li]mites instead of [br]anches.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0007-ptr" id="GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0007">7</a>

   <p>See <a href="default.xqy?keys=GEWN-print-02-08-02-0289&amp;expandNote=GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003#GEWN-02-08-02-0289-fn-0003" class="document">note 3</a>.</p>

